definitions.definition: ( also attributively ) An alloy coating made of lead and tin (or, more recently, zinc and tin), often with some antimony , used to cover iron or steel .
Synonym of terneplate ( “ thin iron or steel sheeting coated with this alloy ” ) .

main_definition: ( also attributively ) An alloy coating made of lead and tin (or, more recently, zinc and tin), often with some antimony , used to cover iron or steel .
secondary_definitions: Synonym of terneplate ( “ thin iron or steel sheeting coated with this alloy ” ) .

definitions.definition: Obsolete spelling of tern ( “ any of various seabirds of the subfamily Sternidae (of the family Laridae ) that are similar to gulls but are smaller and have a forked tail ” ) .

main_definition: Obsolete spelling of tern ( “ any of various seabirds of the subfamily Sternidae (of the family Laridae ) that are similar to gulls but are smaller and have a forked tail ” ) . [17th c.]
